OL,5, PwC has hit back at comments by Lord   
OL,6, Alan Sugar in which he branded its     
OL,7, staff "lazy gits", after the           
OL,8, accountancy giant said workers could   
OL,9, take Friday afternoons off over summer.
OL,11,FThe firm made the offer to its 22,000  
OL,12,FUK staff last week on the condition    
OL,13,Fthey get their work done by lunchtime. 
OL,15,FIn a tweet, the Apprentice host and    
OL,16,Fbusinessman called the move a "joke",  
OL,17,Fsaying it would harm productivity.     
OL,19,FBut PwC said it had worked well in     
OL,20,Ftrials.                                
